# Project Overview
This is a macOS app for AI chat with agentic capabilities. It's written in Swift and uses a simple build system (`build.sh`). The UI is defined entirely in code — there are no XIBs or Storyboards.

The app is under active development, so backwards compatibility is not a concern when making changes.

# Target Platform
macOS 15 or higher. Feel free to use modern APIs and UI components available on this version.

# Dependencies
Dependencies and their documentation live under `.build/checkouts`.

# Chat Rendering
Chat messages are rendered using a webview that loads the web app from `chatrenderer`.

# Building
Use `build.sh` to build the project (this also builds `chatrenderer`). Check the output for compilation errors — no need to pipe through `tail`, `head`, or `2>&1`, as the output is short and errors appear in stdout.

# Research & Experimentation
For quick research, use one-liners with `swift -e`. For anything longer, write a temporary Swift file and run it.

# Code Style
Keep comments minimal. Don't describe the obvious — focus only on:
- Complex or non-obvious behavior
- Architectural decisions
- Things genuinely worth noting

# General Guidance
Don't overthink. If something is unclear, ask. If you hit a difficult problem, explain it first and ask for advice before proceeding.